data.description: This wonderful family home is located in the highly desirable Sanderlin Mountain Neighborhood with views to Amicalola Falls State Park and beyond. This is a RARE opportunity to Live on Sanderlin Mountain.  Homes rarely become available in this part of Big Canoe.  With only three homes on the street, you'll enjoy the peace and quiet of the natural environment as local wildlife passes by daily. The owners of this property have added many features and updates as well as replaced such components as the Roof, HVAC System, Plumbing Fixtures, Driveway, Retaining Walls and Painted the Entire Exterior. In addition,  they've added approximately 1,000 Sq. Ft. of Decking, Increased the Insulation, Updated Bathrooms, installed a Whole House Circulating Pump and Manifold System for all the plumbing outlets,  Plantation Shutters, Cedar Lined All The Closets and completely Renovated The Kitchen. Within the three levels of living space you'll find a Main Level Vaulted Great Room with Stacked Stone Fireplace, Large Primary Suite, an oversized Keeping Room with Gas Fireplace that adjoins the beautiful Cook's Kitchen and Separate Office. A spacious Dining Room, Laundry Room, Half Bath and an Open Deck complete the main level. The Upper Level offers Two Bedrooms, an expanded Jack & Jill Bath and a Large Floored Walk-in Storage Area Over the Garage. The Terrace Level provides a tremendous Family Room with a Cast Iron Gas heater, Bedroom, Full Bath, Storage/Workshop  and a very large partially Covered Deck. Please review the photos and come for a look. As a bonus, this home is located in Dawson County with all its Tax Benefits!
